          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Best Way To Treat Cavities In Seniors</summary>
            <div class="faq-body"><p>Regular exams and specialized care help prevent and treat cavities in older adults, particularly those near the tooth root. Our team offers comprehensive care tailored to senior patients.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Do Baby Teeth Matter</summary>
            <div class="faq-body"><p>Even though baby teeth eventually fall out, decay can spread and affect adult teeth beneath them. Treating cavities in baby teeth is essential for overall dental health.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>It's Serious Only If I Have Pain</summary>
            <div class="faq-body"><p>A cavity can grow silently without causing pain initially. Regular dental exams can catch these early, less painful stages, allowing for simpler treatments.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details open>
            <summary>Removing Teeth Is Easier Than Treating Cavities</summary>
